    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-11T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-11T10:00:00-05:00" n="26"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d26">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/549</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Denmark</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_EMF1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Egan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-11T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 11, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 12, 2.10 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>568. At a conference to-day at Copenhagen between German and Russian Socialists,
                    the German Socialists stated that they would endeavor to move the German
                    Reichstag to consent to peace on the following terms, provided the Russian
                    Socialists would make a similar effort in Russia.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>Germany shall evacuate the occupied territories in northern France and
                        Belgium, which latter country shall be reestablished as an independent state
                        but without the right to maintain an army. Alsace-Lorraine shall remain
                        German. Poland to be reestablished on the basis of its original boundaries:
                        excepted however are the Polish provinces which were held by Germany before
                        the war. Poland shall have no right to maintain an army. The Russian Baltic
                        provinces shall be surrendered to Germany. Bulgaria,<note n="1"
                            xml:id="d26fn1">On Apr. 12, in his telegram No. 573, the Minister added:
                            “Read Bosnia and Herzegovina instead of Bulgaria. In addition Roumania
                            was to be reestablished.” (File No. 763.72119/551.)</note> Servia, and
                        Montenegro to be united in one kingdom called Great Servia under Austrian
                        protection. The Dardanelles to be neutralized and under Turkish supervision.
                        Armenia shall be reestablished also under Turkish supervision.</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_EMF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Egan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
